German FDP Says Government Shouldn’t Recapitalize Banks, HB Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-10-08T10:20:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-08/german-fdp-says-government-shouldn-t-recapitalize-banks-hb-says.html
The German Free  Democratic Party ’s
finance spokesman,  Frank Schaeffler , said the state shouldn’t
help to recapitalize struggling banks,  Handelsblatt  reported,
citing an interview.  Failing banks should be managed in an orderly insolvency
procedure, Schaeffler said, according to the newspaper. The FDP
is the coalition partner of  Chancellor Angela Merkel ’s Christian
Democrats.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  